<li id="cite_note-horwitz-11"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-horwitz_11-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-horwitz_11-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-horwitz_11-2"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-horwitz_11-3"><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-horwitz_11-4"><sup><i><b>e</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-horwitz_11-5"><sup><i><b>f</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><span class="citation Journal">Horwitz, Paul (Fall 1997). "Scientology in Court: A Comparative Analysis and Some Thoughts on Selected Issues in Law and Religion". <i>DePaul Law Review</i> <b>47</b>: 85.</span></span></li>
